runs.comm: yorker to start with from Rankin, Fletcher clips the ball to mid-on and the home team are away with a single
angled across the left-hander, Chanderpaul walks across and tries to work to leg, but only gets it back to the bowler

a nice cover-drive from Chanderpaul, finds the gap and the ball looks like it will reach the boundary until Cusack hauls it in and flicks it to Wilson, who also has to flick it back, but between them they keep it to three
flicked away off the pads, too straight from Rankin
beautiful yorker from Rankin, all Fletcher can do is keep that one out
another single worked away to square leg, nothing too drastic from Andre Fletcher yet, although he's capable of some power-hitting
slower ball from Trent Johnston to start, Fletcher defends
on the hips, Fletcher clips away to short fine leg
Chanderpaul walks across and doesn't connect properly, the ball bobs out to the off side off his pad
pushed back past the bowler but can't beat mid-on
126kph from Johnston, and on this slow pitch a bowler of his speed could be hard to get away - this one beats Chanderpaul outside off
glanced away behind square leg for a single
no hurry from Chanderpaul here, he pushes to cover
goes for a more expansive drive here, it's knocked down by the man at mid-off and Chanderpaul gets two
prodded back down the pitch
this time Chanderpaul finds the gap for the first boundary of the match, Rankin bowled too straight and it's clipped off the pads through midwicket
another poor ball, Rankin goes for the bouncer but it's too slow and too leg-side, and Chanderpaul helps it on its way with a pull to fine leg
Rankin breaks through! Chanderpaul looks to turn a third consecutive delivery to leg but gets top edge, the ball is skied to cover point and Wilson takes the catch
outside off, Bravo defends
straighter line now, Bravo works a single out through midwicket
flicked away to short fine leg
straight ball, clipped off the pads through square leg
defended this time, it's not any easy pitch to score on as the ball really isn't coming on to the bat with any pace
lovely shot! Bravo creates a way to score, driving a half-volley straight down the ground and making no attempt to keep it down, he's cleared the rope
too straight, Fletcher has no trouble driving that on the up wide of mid-on for a boundary
better line now and that's defended
quick single, Fletcher was on the back foot dropping that one to leg, but he made his ground as the keeper's throw to the bowler's end didn't hit
glanced off the pads to fine leg, Gary Wilson runs around and cuts it off
tries to guide this one through the vacant slips but gets too much of it and pushes to gully
Bravo drives to mid-on, looks to use his strength to force that one but can't beat the fielder
short and wide, Bravo throws everything at that one and it's cleared the rope at extra cover! A six over cover, wonderful shot!

Cusack's caught him, has he? Yes he has, eventually! Bravo drives straight and the ball holds up on the pitch, the bowler goes for the return catch and doesn't take it cleanly, in fact he's juggled and it's bounced off his belly as was doing an army roll, but he's held on to it!
prodded back down the pitch
angled in to Sarwan, who pushes away defensively
straight ball, straight bat, lovely line from Cusack
slowish ball, but most are from Cusack, and Sarwan can't get it away
tossed up outside off, it's pushed away for a single
Sarwan lunges forward and guides a single to leg
prodded back to the bowler
nudged away to midwicket, there's some pressure building here
shortish ball, Fletcher should have put that away and all he can do is get it to midwicket where a misfield allows a single
turned behind square leg for one
stump to stump stuff again, Sarwan drives to long-on
and Fletcher drives to the other side, long-off
another drive to long-off and they push through for two, really they should have been looking for a couple off the first two balls of the over as well, try to put some pressure on the fielders
pushed away to cover
tries to force this one through cover off the back foot, can't beat the field
another drive to long-off, this time Wilson keeps it to a single
Sarwan waits on this delivery and deftly guides it towards third man
some power this time, goes over wide midwicket but the sweeper cuts off the boundary
and again Sarwan helps it through third man, lovely stuff, he's handling the spin much better than Fletcher
wide down leg side
this ball stays a bit low, worked behind square leg
and more bounce this time, punched back down the pitch
again Sarwan backs away and looks to cut fine, might have been an edgier shot than he intended but it means the ball has travelled fine enough to beat third man
guided fine, but can't beat fine leg
that ball has stayed really low, Fletcher can only push it down towards long-on
Dockrell is around the wicket, not much spin and Sarwan cuts fine, lovely touch
nicely timed, just an aerial drive over wide mid-off, more of a chip really and he gets two
down leg side, can't get it away
another quick single pushed to point
off the back foot, Sarwan forces it down the ground to long-on
straight ball and Fletcher walks across, clips over midwicket but there's a man on the boundary, dangerous one if he didn't connect
another single down the ground, the boundaries really are proving hard to come by with the lack of pace in the pitch

in the air, is it six, is it out? Neither! Fletcher lifted that one off his pads towards wide midwicket, Wilson running around on the boundary couldn't get there for the catch but did well to knock it back into the field on the bounce
overpitched, looking for the yorker now and a full toss is worked through leg
slow bouncer there, and when I say slow, I mean almost stationary! Sarwan had to wait an age for that to reach him, when it did he's swatted it baseball style through midwicket
lofted down the ground to long-off

the teenage Dockrell gets the wicket! Fletcher went for the big aerial drive, tried to clear long-on but he hasn't quite got hold of it, Kevin O'Brien takes a well-judged catch a couple of steps in from the boundary
pushed away to cover
another one! Two in three balls from Dockrell! Sarwan this time tries to go over the top but doesn't time it, Wilson takes the catch at deep mid-off
over the wicket to the left-hander Deonarine, defended back to the bowler
nudged away to point for a single
pushed to cover for a quick single
driven to long-on for a single
big appeal! Down the leg side and Ireland are convinced there was glove on that, Billy Bowden disagrees but doesn't call a wide, so he must have felt there was some thigh-pad
driven powerfully through point
on the pads, Deonarine glances down to fine leg
gone! Oh dear! Terrible ball, really, it was a long way down leg side and Ramdin went for the glance, the keeper was utterly convinced that had come off the face of the bat and so was Bowden.
almost! Oh, an inside edge there from Deonarine and it's gone through the legs of the keeper! Probably didn't have any chance to take that
prodded back down the pitch to Dockrell
gets this one away for one
driven down the ground for another single
driven down the ground to long-on
Deonarine punches this one through point for one more
can't get this one away
straight line, not giving West Indies anything, and it's pushed to mid-off
slower ball, again Deonarine cannot beat the field
holding up off the pitch again, Deonarine tries to flick through leg but no run
shorter ball, but all the batsman can to is whip it to deep midwicket for a single
Sammy crunches this one forward of point but again can't find the boundary
no run again, can't beat the field
on the pads, Sammy tries to flick it away but backward square leg does the fielding
beat the bat outside off
this one bobs up through midwicket
nudged back to the bowler

Dockrell gets his third, what a good spell! Deonarine realised that he was getting bogged down and went for the slog sweep, the top edge was skied and Niall O'Brien took it comfortably with the gloves
watchful first ball, Pollard defends
walks across and just works a single to square leg
finally a boundary! Sammy connects on a shortish, slowish ball and swivels a pull through midwicket to the boundary
bad ball from Rankin, too full and wide down leg, Sammy does well to get anything on that, just helps it to the fine-leg boundary
shorter on the hips, nudged to square leg for a single
lovely placement and timing from Pollard, he's flicked the ball off his pads and managed to find the gap between backward square and deep midwicket

excellent timing from Sammy, half-volley outside off and Sammy drives hard and straight, clears the long-off boundary. In fact, that ball has smashed a window in the stand! "Into the lunch-room," says Ian Bishop
pulls to square leg this time
goes for the yorker, it turns into a low full toss on the stumps and Sammy drives a single to long off
not a bad ball, straight and yorkerish length, Pollard manages to clip through midwicket and puts the pressure on the fielder to get back for two
caught? No! Pollard swats it flat and hard to deep square leg, Stirling dives and does well to make the stop as the ball bounces a few inches in front of him
that's what the crowd wants to see! Darren Sammy is upstaging Kieron Pollard here, with a wonderful, powerful pull off the back foot and over wide midwicket and into the stands
Pollard's gone, Botha gets the breakthrough. Back of a length and slowish off the pitch, Pollard top-edges his attempted pull and Botha runs back towards the stumps to take a simple return catch
crunched away through point

oh, Sammy's gone too! That's a very handy wicket for Ireland to keep this total down. He's tried for the pull over long-on but the slower pace has deceived Sammy, who picks out the man on the boundary
clipped for a single through square leg
straight ball, and pushed back to the bowler by Rampaul
flicked through backward square for a couple
goes for the slog, top-edged out through the off side
full and well wide of off, O'Brien does really well to take that ball and Ireland are lucky to get away with that, could have been called a wide
beats Rampaul this time with a good full ball
oops, this one might've slipped out of Cusack's hand, it's a full toss around chest height, Rampaul, gets it to long-off for two and they will get a bonus delivery
driven down the ground for a couple more
Rampaul charges, Cusack delivers a yorker but it's driven to long-on for two more
and a wicket to finish the innings, Rampaul looks to clear the leg-side field but his top-edge is taken at mid-on
